                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.512/429: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-10-29T11:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 29, 1926—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 29—1:03 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>519. Following from American consul general, Canton: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“October 28, 1 p.m. Guise of preventing traffic in opium, Chen announces
                            the establishment by the Ministry of Finance of inspection stations at
                            Dosing and Hotow, West River, at which all passing steamers of every
                            nationality are required to stop and undergo inspection. Portuguese
                            consul favors joint protest immediately, but the other interested
                            consuls prefer first consulting their respective Legations. Despatch
                            will be forwarded.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mayer</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
